cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on evaluating the quality of real-time streaming in wireless cellular networks, which is a networking problem. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper mentions the theoretical Shannon's bound in the additive white Gaussian noise (AWGN) channel, which is a concept from information theory. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper specifically mentions mobile TV as an example of real-time streaming, which falls under the category of multimedia. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses resource allocation policies for managing interruptions and capacity sharing, which is a control problem. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper evaluates several performance characteristics of the stochastic service model, such as mean time spent in outage and mean number of outage incidents, which falls under the category of performance analysis.
